s in Czechoslovakia]]\n[[Category:Social history of the Czech Republic]]\n[[Category:Czechoslovakia\u2013Germany relations]]\n[[Category:Munich Agreement]]\n", "name_user": "Arjayay", "label": "safe", "comment": "Duplicate word removed", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Sudeten_Germans"}
{"title_page": "Cuando quiero llorar no lloro (film)", "text_new": "{{short description|1973 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=April 2020}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Cuando quiero llorar no lloro\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Mauricio Walerstein]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = [[Miguel Otero Silva]]<br>Mauricio Walerstein\n| starring       = [[Orlando Urdaneta]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Abigail Rojas\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|1973|7}}\n| runtime        = 85 minutes\n| country        = Venezuela\n| language       = Spanish\n}}\n\n'''''Cuando quiero llorar no lloro''''' (English: ''When I Want To Cry, I Don't'') is a 1973 Venezuelan [[drama film]] directed by [[Mauricio Walerstein]] based in the [[Cuando quiero llorar no lloro|homonymous novel]] by [[Miguel Otero Silva]]. It was entered into the [[8th Moscow International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Moscow1973\">{{cite web|url=http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1973 |title=8th Moscow International Film Festival (1973) |accessdate=3 January 2013 |work=MIFF |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130116194922/http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1973 |archivedate=16 January 2013 }}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nIn 1948 Venezuela three children are born on the same day, all named Victorino were born. One is a poor [[mulatto]], Victorino Perez; the second is Victorino Perdomo, from a middle class communist family; and the third is Victorino Peralta, of society's upper echelons.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dequevalapeli.com/canon/ver/OTA1|title=Cuando quiero llorar no lloro (1973); ?>|last=Dequevalapeli|website=dequevalapeli.com|language=es|access-date=31 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nEighteen years later, the three are living very different lives. Perez is in and out of prison and violent situations from childhood; Perdomo falls from middle-class grace as communism is rejected; Peralta spends much of his time surrounded by luxury and many women, ensconced in the same violence as the other Victorinos but never getting in trouble. However, all three die young: Perez shot when running from police, Perdomo tortured by enemies, and Peralta crashed his car dreaming of being a boy racer.\n\n==Cast==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=35em|\n* [[Orlando Urdaneta]] as Victorino Perez\n* [[Pedro Laya]] as Victorino Perdomo\n* [[Valentin Trujillo]] as Victorino Peralta\n* [[Fernando Arriaga]]\n* [[Hayd\u00e9e Balza]]\n* [[Rafael Brice\u00f1o]]\n* [[Miguel \u00c1ngel Landa]]\n* [[Liliana Dur\u00e1n]]\n* [[Ver\u00f3nica Castro]]\n* [[Andres Toro]]\n* [[Jesus Tadeo]]\n* [[Zulma Sady]]\n* [[Hilda Rivas]]\n* [[Esther Plaza]]\n* [[Luis Pardi]]\n* [[Guillermo Montiel]]\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0068432}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cuando Quiero Ilorar No Iloro}}\n[[Category:1973 films]]\n[[Category:1973 drama films]]\n[[Category:Venezuelan films]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language films]]\n[[Category:Venezuelan drama films]]\n{{Venezuela-film-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{short description|1973 film}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=October 2019}}\n{{Infobox film\n| name           = Cuando quiero llorar no lloro\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| director       = [[Mauricio Walerstein]]\n| producer       = \n| writer         = [[Miguel Otero Silva]]<br>Mauricio Walerstein\n| starring       = [[Orlando Urdaneta]]\n| music          = \n| cinematography = Abigail Rojas\n| editing        = \n| distributor    = \n| released       = {{Film date|df=yes|1973|7}}\n| runtime        = 85 minutes\n| country        = Venezuela\n| language       = Spanish\n}}\n\n'''''Cuando quiero llorar no lloro''''' (English: ''When I Want To Cry, I Don't'') is a 1973 Venezuelan [[drama film]] directed by [[Mauricio Walerstein]] based in the [[Cuando quiero llorar no lloro|homonymous novel]] by [[Miguel Otero Silva]]. It was entered into the [[8th Moscow International Film Festival]].<ref name=\"Moscow1973\">{{cite web|url=http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1973 |title=8th Moscow International Film Festival (1973) |accessdate=3 January 2013 |work=MIFF |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130116194922/http://www.moscowfilmfestival.ru/miff34/eng/archives/?year=1973 |archivedate=16 January 2013 }}</ref>\n\n==Plot==\nIn 1948 Venezuela three children are born on the same day, all named Victorino were born. One is a poor [[mulatto]], Victorino Perez; the second is Victorino Perdomo, from a middle class communist family; and the third is Victorino Peralta, of society's upper echelons.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://dequevalapeli.com/canon/ver/OTA1|title=Cuando quiero llorar no lloro (1973); ?>|last=Dequevalapeli|website=dequevalapeli.com|language=es|access-date=31 August 2019}}</ref>\n\nEighteen years later, the three are living very different lives. Perez is in and out of prison and violent situations from childhood; Perdomo falls from middle-class grace as communism is rejected; Peralta spends much of his time surrounded by luxury and many women, ensconced in the same violence as the other Victorinos but never getting in trouble. However, all three die young: Perez shot when running from police, Perdomo tortured by enemies, and Peralta crashed his car dreaming of being a boy racer.\n\n==Cast==\n{{columns-list|colwidth=35em|\n* [[Orlando Urdaneta]] as Victorino Perez\n* [[Pedro Laya]] as Victorino Perdomo\n* [[Valentin Trujillo]] as Victorino Peralta\n* [[Fernando Arriaga]]\n* [[Hayd\u00e9e Balza]]\n* [[Rafael Brice\u00f1o]]\n* [[Miguel \u00c1ngel Landa]]\n* [[Liliana Dur\u00e1n]]\n* [[Ver\u00f3nica Castro]]\n* [[Andres Toro]]\n* [[Jesus Tadeo]]\n* [[Zulma Sady]]\n* [[Hilda Rivas]]\n* [[Esther Plaza]]\n* [[Luis Pardi]]\n* [[Guillermo Montiel]]\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{IMDb title|0068432}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Cuando Quiero Ilorar No Iloro}}\n[[Category:1973 films]]\n[[Category:1973 drama films]]\n[[Category:Venezuelan films]]\n[[Category:Spanish-language films]]\n[[Category:Venezuelan drama films]]\n{{Venezuela-film-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Lugnuts", "label": "safe", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Cuando_quiero_llorar_no_lloro_(film)"}
{"title_page": "Thornhill (electoral district)", "text_new": "{{for|the provincial electoral district|Thornhill (provincial electoral district)}}\n{{Infobox Canada electoral district\n| name                = Thornhill\n| province            = Ontario\n| image               = Thornhill 2015.svg\n| caption             = Thornhill in relation to other [[Greater Toronto Area|Greater Toronto]] ridings\n| fed-status          = active\n| fed-district-number = 35104\n| fed-created         = 1996\n| fed-abolished       = \n| fed-election-first  = 1997\n| fed-election-last   = 2019\n| fed-rep             = Peter Kent\n| fed-rep-link        = \n| fed-rep-party       = Conservative\n| fed-rep-party-link  = Conservative Party of Canada\n| demo-pop-ref        = <ref name=pop>{{cite web|url=https://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2016/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=FED&Code1=35104&Geo2=PR&Code2=35&SearchText=thornhill&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&B1=All&TABID=1&type=0|title=Census Profile, 2016 Census ''Thornhill''|publisher= Statistics Canada|date= 2016| |accessdate=4 December 2018}}</ref>\n| demo-area-ref       = <ref name=pop/>\n| demo-electors-ref   = \n| demo-census-date    = [[Canada 2016 Census|2016]]\n| demo-pop            = 112719\n| demo-electors       = 80288\n| demo-electors-date  = 2015\n| demo-area           = 62.90\n| demo-cd             = [[Regional Municipality of York|York]]\n| demo-csd            = [[Markham, Ontario|Markham]], [[Vaughan]]\n}}\n\n[[Image:Thornhill, riding.png|thumb|right|250px|Thornhill 2003 to 2015]]\n[[Image:Thornhill (riding map).png|thumb|right|250px|Map of Thornhill riding (2003 boundaries)]]\n\n'''Thornhill''' is a federal [[electoral district (Canada)|electoral district]] in [[Ontario]], Canada, that has been represented in the [[House of Commons of Canada]] since 1997.\n\nIt consists of the part of the city of Vaughan that is east of [[Ontario Highway 400|Highway 400]] and south of Rutherford Road, and the part of the city of Markham west of [[Bayview Avenue]].\n\nIt covers the [[Thornhill, Ontario|Thornhill]] neighbourhood, which is split between [[Vaughan]] and [[Markham, Ontario|Markham]], and was created in 1996 and the east end of the riding was split off into other ridings in 2012.\n\nIt is one of only two ridings in Canada with a [[Judaism|Jewish]] plurality (the other being [[Mount Royal (electoral district)|Mount Royal]] in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]]), with 32.8% of the population identifying as Jewish, the highest in Canada.<ref>http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/nhs-enm/2011/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=FED&Code1=35089&Data=Count&SearchText=Thornhill&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&A1=All&B1=All&Custom=&TABID=1</ref> Thornhill also has the highest percentage of Russians (12.9%) of all Canadian ridings (implying the presence of a strong community of [[History of the Jews in Russia|Russian Jews]]<ref>http://www2.kolel.org/home.do;jsessionid=382A7EA91B61739609208258AB0A89AF?ch=events&state=organizationSearch&Submit=show&organization=1761</ref>).\n\nThe Thornhill riding has the highest percentage of population with an educational attainment of \"University certificate or diploma above bachelor level\" (i.e. above-bachelor-level certificate or diploma other than doctorate, master, or medicine etc. degrees) with 5.0%.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2006/dp-pd/tbt/Rp-eng.cfm?LANG=E&APATH=3&DETAIL=0&DIM=0&FL=A&FREE=0&GC=0&GID=0&GK=0&GRP=1&PID=93713&PRID=0&PTYPE=88971,97154&S=0&SHOWALL=0&SUB=0&Temporal=2006&THEME=75&VID=0&VNAMEE=&VNAMEF= |title=2006 Census of Canada: Topic-based tabulations &#124; Highest Certificate, Diploma or Degree (14), Location of Study (5), Major Field of Study - Classification of Instructional Programs, 2000 (14), Age Groups (10A) and Sex (3) for the Population 15 Years and Over of Canada, Provinces, Territories and Federal Electoral Districts (2003 Representation Order), 2006 Census - 20% Sample Data |publisher=2.statcan.gc.ca |accessdate=2012-11-16}}</ref>\n\n==Demographics==\n:''According to the [[Canada 2011 Census]]''; 2013 representation<ref>http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/nhs-enm/2011/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=FED2013&Code1=35104&Data=Count&SearchText=Thornhill&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&A1=All&B1=All&Custom=&TABID=1</ref><ref>http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/nhs-enm/2011/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=FED2013&Code1=35104&Data=Count&SearchText=Thornhill&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&A1=All&B1=All&Custom=&TABID=1#tabs2</ref>''\n\n'''Ethnic groups:''' 68.2% White, 7.6% Chinese, 6.5% South Asian, 4.6% Filipino, 3.7% Korean, 3.3% West Asian, 1.9% Black, 1.1% Southeast Asian<br />\n'''Languages:''' 49.9% English, 13.0% Russian, 6.2% Chinese, 3.1% [[Persian language|Persian]], 3.2% Korean, 3.7% Hebrew, 3.0% Italian, 2.2% Tagalog, 1.7% Spanish 1.4% French, 1.0% Gujarati<br />\n'''Religions:''' 37.5% Christian (18.8% Catholic, 6.2% Christian Orthodox, 2.0% Presbyterian, 1.6% Anglican, 1.5% United Church, 7.3% Other Christian), 37.1% Jewish, 4.3% Muslim, 3.4% Hindu, 2.0% Buddhist, 14.7% None. <br />\n'''Median income:''' $30,798 (2010) <br />\n'''Average income:''' $47,097  (2010)\n\n==History==\nThe riding was first established in the 1996 redistribution from parts of [[York North]] and [[Markham\u2014Whitchurch\u2014Stouffville]].<ref name=1993elec>{{cite map|title=Results of the 35th Federal Election |publisher=Elections Canada |scale=1:7,500,000 |url=http://ftp.geogratis.gc.ca/pub/nrcan_rncan/raster/atlas/eng/federal_election/mcr_0196.pdf |access-date=April 19, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"1996rd\">{{cite web |title=Thornhill ELECTORAL DISTRICT NO. 35085 |url=http://www.elections.ca/scripts/info/edMap_e.asp?edID=35085 |website=elections.ca |publisher=Elections Canada |accessdate=April 19, 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010628024530/http://www.elections.ca/scripts/info/edMap_e.asp?edID=35085 |archivedate=June 28, 2001}}</ref> The area of the riding was not affected by the 2003 electoral redistribution.<ref name=1996rd/><ref name=\"2003rd\">{{cite web |title=Thornhill \u2013 Historical data |url=https://www.elections.ca/res/cir/maps/mapprov.asp?map=35089&lang=e |website=elections.ca |publisher=Elections Canada |accessdate=April 19, 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190612134050/https://www.elections.ca/res/cir/maps/mapprov.asp?map=35089&lang=e |archivedate=June 12, 2019 |date=2003 |url-status=live}}</ref> During the [[Canadian federal electoral redistribution, 2012|2012 redistribution]], the area of the riding east of [[Bayview Avenue]] was transferred to [[Richmond Hill (electoral district)|Richmond Hill]] north of [[Ontario Highway 407|Highway 407]] and the new riding of [[Markham\u2014Thornhill]] south of Highway 407.<ref name=2003rd/><ref name=\"2013rd\">{{cite web |author1=Ontario Electoral Redistribution Commission |title=Federal Redistribution Map - York |url=http://www.redecoupage-federal-redistribution.ca/on/now/reports/21York.pdf |website=2012 electoral district redistribution |accessdate=April 19, 2020 |archiveurl=http://www.redecoupage-federal-redistribution.ca/on/now/reports/21York.pdf |archivedate=December 11, 2017 |date=2012-2013 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Members of Parliament==\n\nThis riding has elected the following members of the [[House of Commons of Canada]]:\n\n{{CanMP}}\n{{CanMP nodata|Thornhill<br />''Riding created from'' [[Markham\u2014Whitchurch\u2014Stouffville]]<br />''and'' [[York North]]}}\n{{CanMP row\n| FromYr = 1997\n| ToYr = 2000\n| Assembly# = 36\n| CanParty = Liberal\n| RepName = Elinor Caplan\n| RepTerms# = 2\n| PartyTerms# = 4\n}}\n{{CanMP row\n| FromYr = 2000\n| ToYr = 2004\n| Assembly# = 37\n}}\n{{CanMP row\n| FromYr = 2004\n| ToYr = 2006\n| Assembly# = 38\n| RepName = Susan Kadis\n| RepTerms# = 2\n}}\n{{CanMP row\n| FromYr = 2006\n| ToYr = 2008\n| Assembly# = 39\n}}\n{{CanMP row\n| FromYr = 2008\n| ToYr = 2011\n| Assembly# = 40\n| CanParty = Conservative\n| Rep