}\n{{CANelec|CA|Liberal|[[Elinor Caplan]] |27,152|64.59|+5.59}}\n{{CANelec|CA|Canadian Alliance|Robert Goldin|6,643|15.80|+7.91}}\n{{CANelec|CA|PC|Lou Watson|6,338|15.08|-11.31}}\n{{CANelec|CA|NDP|Nathan Rotman|1,653|3.93|-0.67}}\n{{CANelec|CA|Canadian Action|Art Jaszczyk|254|0.60|}}\n{{Canadian election result/total|Total valid votes|42,040 |100.00}}\n{{end}}\nNote: Canadian Alliance vote is compared to the Reform vote in 1997 election.\t\t\n\t\t\t\t\t\n{{Canadian election result/top|CA|1997|percent=yes}}\n{{CANelec|CA|Liberal|[[Elinor Caplan]] |25,747|59.00}}\n{{CANelec|CA|PC|Bill Fisch|11,517|26.39}}\n{{CANelec|CA|Reform|Aurel David|3,441|7.89}}\n{{CANelec|CA|NDP|Helen Breslauer|2,008|4.60}}\n{{CANelec|CA|Independent|Rick Levine|303|0.69}}\n{{CANelec|CA|Natural Law|Linda Martin|261|0.60}}\n{{CANelec|CA|Independent|Sid Soban|238|0.55}}\n{{CANelec|CA|Independent|Shel Bergson|124|0.28}}\n{{Canadian election result/total|Total valid votes|43,639 |100.00}}\n{{end}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of Canadian federal electoral districts]]\n* [[Past Canadian electoral districts]]\n\n==References==\n\n{{reflist}}\n\n==Sources==\n*[http://www2.parl.gc.ca/Sites/LOP/HFER/hfer.asp?Language=E&Search=Det&Include=Y&rid=1069 Riding history from the] [[Library of Parliament]]\n* [http://enr.elections.ca/ElectoralDistricts_e.aspx?type=3&criteria=Thornhill 2011 results from Elections Canada]\n* [www.elections.ca Campaign expense data from Elections Canada]\n\n{{Ridings in Southern Durham and York}}\n{{Ridings in Ontario}}\n\n{{coord|43.8112|N|79.4236|W|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Ontario federal electoral districts]]\n[[Category:Politics of Markham, Ontario]]\n[[Category:Politics of Vaughan]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the provincial electoral district|Thornhill (provincial electoral district)}}\n{{Infobox Canada electoral district\n| name                = Thornhill\n| province            = Ontario\n| image               = Thornhill 2015.svg\n| caption             = Thornhill in relation to other [[Greater Toronto Area|Greater Toronto]] ridings\n| fed-status          = active\n| fed-district-number = 35104\n| fed-created         = 1996\n| fed-abolished       = \n| fed-election-first  = 1997\n| fed-election-last   = 2019\n| fed-rep             = Peter Kent\n| fed-rep-link        = \n| fed-rep-party       = Conservative\n| fed-rep-party-link  = Conservative Party of Canada\n| demo-pop-ref        = <ref name=pop>{{cite web|url=https://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2016/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=FED&Code1=35104&Geo2=PR&Code2=35&SearchText=thornhill&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&B1=All&TABID=1&type=0|title=Census Profile, 2016 Census ''Thornhill''|publisher= Statistics Canada|date= 2016| |accessdate=4 December 2018}}</ref>\n| demo-area-ref       = <ref name=pop/>\n| demo-electors-ref   = \n| demo-census-date    = [[Canada 2016 Census|2016]]\n| demo-pop            = 112719\n| demo-electors       = 80288\n| demo-electors-date  = 2015\n| demo-area           = 62.90\n| demo-cd             = [[Regional Municipality of York|York]]\n| demo-csd            = [[Markham, Ontario|Markham]], [[Vaughan]]\n}}\n\n[[Image:Thornhill, riding.png|thumb|right|250px|Thornhill 2003 to 2015]]\n[[Image:Thornhill (riding map).png|thumb|right|250px|Map of Thornhill riding (2003 boundaries)]]\n\n'''Thornhill''' is a federal [[electoral district (Canada)|electoral district]] in [[Ontario]], Canada, that has been represented in the [[House of Commons of Canada]] since 1997.\n\nIt consists of the part of the city of Vaughan that is east of [[Ontario Highway 400|Highway 400]] and south of Rutherford Road, and the part of the city of Markham west of [[Bayview Avenue]].\n\nIt covers the [[Thornhill, Ontario|Thornhill]] neighbourhood, which is split between [[Vaughan]] and [[Markham, Ontario|Markham]], and was created in 1996 and the east end of the riding was split off into other ridings in 2012.\n\nIt is one of only two ridings in Canada with a [[Judaism|Jewish]] plurality (the other being [[Mount Royal (electoral district)|Mount Royal]] in [[Montreal]], [[Quebec]]), with 32.8% of the population identifying as Jewish, the highest in Canada.<ref>http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/nhs-enm/2011/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=FED&Code1=35089&Data=Count&SearchText=Thornhill&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&A1=All&B1=All&Custom=&TABID=1</ref> Thornhill also has the highest percentage of Russians (12.9%) of all Canadian ridings (implying the presence of a strong community of [[History of the Jews in Russia|Russian Jews]]<ref>http://www2.kolel.org/home.do;jsessionid=382A7EA91B61739609208258AB0A89AF?ch=events&state=organizationSearch&Submit=show&organization=1761</ref>).\n\nThe Thornhill riding has the highest percentage of population with an educational attainment of \"University certificate or diploma above bachelor level\" (i.e. above-bachelor-level certificate or diploma other than doctorate, master, or medicine etc. degrees) with 5.0%.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/census-recensement/2006/dp-pd/tbt/Rp-eng.cfm?LANG=E&APATH=3&DETAIL=0&DIM=0&FL=A&FREE=0&GC=0&GID=0&GK=0&GRP=1&PID=93713&PRID=0&PTYPE=88971,97154&S=0&SHOWALL=0&SUB=0&Temporal=2006&THEME=75&VID=0&VNAMEE=&VNAMEF= |title=2006 Census of Canada: Topic-based tabulations &#124; Highest Certificate, Diploma or Degree (14), Location of Study (5), Major Field of Study - Classification of Instructional Programs, 2000 (14), Age Groups (10A) and Sex (3) for the Population 15 Years and Over of Canada, Provinces, Territories and Federal Electoral Districts (2003 Representation Order), 2006 Census - 20% Sample Data |publisher=2.statcan.gc.ca |accessdate=2012-11-16}}</ref>\n\n==Demographics==\n:''According to the [[Canada 2011 Census]]''; 2013 representation<ref>http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/nhs-enm/2011/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=FED2013&Code1=35104&Data=Count&SearchText=Thornhill&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&A1=All&B1=All&Custom=&TABID=1</ref><ref>http://www12.statcan.gc.ca/nhs-enm/2011/dp-pd/prof/details/page.cfm?Lang=E&Geo1=FED2013&Code1=35104&Data=Count&SearchText=Thornhill&SearchType=Begins&SearchPR=01&A1=All&B1=All&Custom=&TABID=1#tabs2</ref>''\n\n'''Ethnic groups:''' 68.2% White, 7.6% Chinese, 6.5% South Asian, 4.6% Filipino, 3.7% Korean, 3.3% West Asian, 1.9% Black, 1.1% Southeast Asian<br />\n'''Languages:''' 49.9% English, 13.0% Russian, 6.2% Chinese, 3.1% [[Persian language|Persian]], 3.2% Korean, 3.7% Hebrew, 3.0% Italian, 2.2% Tagalog, 1.7% Spanish 1.4% French, 1.0% Gujarati<br />\n'''Religions:''' 37.5% Christian (18.8% Catholic, 6.2% Christian Orthodox, 2.0% Presbyterian, 1.6% Anglican, 1.5% United Church, 7.3% Other Christian), 37.1% Jewish, 4.3% Muslim, 3.4% Hindu, 2.0% Buddhist, 14.7% None. <br />\n'''Median income:''' $30,798 (2010) <br />\n'''Average income:''' $47,097  (2010)\n\n==History==\nThe riding was first established in the 1996 redistribution from parts of [[York North]] and [[Markham\u2014Whitchurch\u2014Stouffville]].<ref name=1993elec>{{cite map|title=Results of the 35th Federal Election |publisher=Elections Canada |scale=1:7,500,000 |url=http://ftp.geogratis.gc.ca/pub/nrcan_rncan/raster/atlas/eng/federal_election/mcr_0196.pdf |access-date=April 19, 2020}}</ref><ref name=\"1996rd\">{{cite web |title=Thornhill ELECTORAL DISTRICT NO. 35085 |url=http://www.elections.ca/scripts/info/edMap_e.asp?edID=35085 |website=elections.ca |publisher=Elections Canada |accessdate=April 19, 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20010628024530/http://www.elections.ca/scripts/info/edMap_e.asp?edID=35085 |archivedate=June 28, 2001}}</ref> The area of the riding was not affected by the 2003 electoral redistribution.<ref name=1996rd/><ref name=\"2003rd\">{{cite web |title=Thornhill \u2013 Historical data |url=https://www.elections.ca/res/cir/maps/mapprov.asp?map=35089&lang=e |website=elections.ca |publisher=Elections Canada |accessdate=April 19, 2020 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20190612134050/https://www.elections.ca/res/cir/maps/mapprov.asp?map=35089&lang=e |archivedate=June 12, 2019 |date=2003 |url-status=live}}</ref> During the the [[Canadian federal electoral redistribution, 2012|2012 redistribution]], the area of the riding east of [[Bayview Avenue]] was transferred to [[Richmond Hill (electoral district)|Richmond Hill]] north of [[Ontario Highway 407|Highway 407]] and the new riding of [[Markham\u2014Thornhill]] south of Highway 407.<ref name=2003rd/><ref name=\"2013rd\">{{cite web |author1=Ontario Electoral Redistribution Commission |title=Federal Redistribution Map - York |url=http://www.redecoupage-federal-redistribution.ca/on/now/reports/21York.pdf |website=2012 electoral district redistribution |accessdate=April 19, 2020 |archiveurl=http://www.redecoupage-federal-redistribution.ca/on/now/reports/21York.pdf |archivedate=December 11, 2017 |date=2012-2013 |url-status=live}}</ref>\n\n==Members of Parliament==\n\nThis riding has elected the following members of the [[House of Commons of Canada]]:\n\n{{CanMP}}\n{{CanMP nodata|Thornhill<br />''Riding created from'' [[Markham\u2014Whitchurch\u2014Stouffville]]<br />''and'' [[York North]]}}\n{{CanMP row\n| FromYr = 1997\n| ToYr = 2000\n| Assembly# = 36\n| CanParty = Liberal\n| RepName = Elinor Caplan\n| RepTerms# = 2\n| PartyTerms# = 4\n}}\n{{CanMP row\n| FromYr = 2000\n| ToYr = 2004\n| Assembly# = 37\n}}\n{{CanMP row\n| FromYr = 2004\n| ToYr = 2006\n| Assembly# = 38\n| RepName = Susan Kadis\n| RepTerms# = 2\n}}\n{{CanMP row\n| FromYr = 2006\n| ToYr = 2008\n| Assembly# = 39\n}}\n{{CanMP row\n| FromYr = 2008\n| ToYr = 2011\n| Assembly# = 40\n| CanParty = Conservative\n| RepName = Peter Kent\n| RepTerms# = 4\n| PartyTerms# = 4\n}}\n{{CanMP row\n| FromYr = 2011\n| ToYr = 2015\n| Assembly# = 41\n}}\n{{CanMP row\n| FromYr = 2015\n| ToYr = 2019\n| Assembly# = 42\n}}\n{{CanMP row\n| FromYr = 2019\n| ToYr = \n| Assembly# = 43\n}}\n{{CanMP end}}\n\n==Election results==\n{{Image frame\n| content = {{Graph:Chart\n |